1
00:00:00,691 --> 00:00:04,619
[Never Too Late]

2
00:00:04,619 --> 00:00:06,099
Xiao Zhang,

3
00:00:06,099 --> 00:00:08,380
come over for dinner when you're free.
[Episode 3]

4
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:09,860
Okay.

5
00:00:09,860 --> 00:00:13,220
Xiao Zhang, let's go fishing together next time.

6
00:00:13,220 --> 00:00:15,240
Definitely, definitely.

7
00:00:15,979 --> 00:00:19,300
I hope I can attend your wedding.

8
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:22,380
- You must come. You must come.
- Yes.

9
00:00:22,380 --> 00:00:25,479
Well, I almost forgot. Wait a moment.

10
00:00:25,479 --> 00:00:27,100
Okay.

11
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:32,420
Also, you and Xile should hurry up too.

12
00:00:32,420 --> 00:00:35,160
- Be good to Xile.
- Okay.

13
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:37,320
Excuse me.

14
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:39,839
Be good to Xile.

15
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:45,860
- Don't forget to take the fish you caught.
- No need. You can keep it and eat it together.

16
00:00:45,860 --> 00:00:48,840
No, it was agreed that the fish caught would be half each. I've already divided it for you.

17
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:51,120
Okay, I'll take it.

18
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:53,800
Uncle, Auntie, Xile, I'm leaving.

19
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:56,200
Okay, take care. Goodbye.

20
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,720
Wait, wait.

21
00:00:57,720 --> 00:01:00,320
Xile, aren't you going to walk him out?

22
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:02,380
He doesn't need me to walk him out.

23
00:01:02,380 --> 00:01:06,059
You ate so much tonight. If you don't go for a walk, you'll get fat.

24
00:01:06,059 --> 00:01:09,060
- Go, go.
- Okay. Ping'an, I'll walk you downstairs.

25
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:10,880
- Okay.
- Be careful, Xiao Zhang.

26
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:12,496
Okay.

27
00:01:14,539 --> 00:01:17,339
Senyun, let's go down and take a look too.

28
00:01:17,339 --> 00:01:19,879
I think this young man is not bad. They're very compatible.

29
00:01:19,879 --> 00:01:25,099
I also think it's pretty good. But Xile said she needed to know more about him.

30
00:01:25,099 --> 00:01:27,860
Qi Fei, where are you? I'll go to see you.

31
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:29,699
I'm not here.

32
00:01:29,699 --> 00:01:33,279
What do you mean you're not here? I'm asking you where you are.

33
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,800
You want to get dressed so quickly.

34
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,980
What do you take me for?

35
00:02:06,159 --> 00:02:08,360
You're so cute.

36
00:02:14,419 --> 00:02:17,100
Drive safely at night.

37
00:02:18,220 --> 00:02:22,280
Thank you for accompanying me fishing today.

38
00:02:23,979 --> 00:02:28,179
Xile, I hope we can go fishing together next time.

39
00:02:28,179 --> 00:02:31,560
Okay, go home first.

40
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:35,160
Okay, you also be careful.

41
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,260
Okay.

42
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:37,960
Bye.

43
00:02:49,862 --> 00:02:52,058
[Zhao Lin]

44
00:02:55,419 --> 00:02:57,260
Lu Liuliu is really…

45
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:59,640
Why send me this kind of message at this time?

46
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:01,460
The robot left?

47
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,679
What robot?

48
00:03:11,679 --> 00:03:13,599
Why do you always stumble?

49
00:03:13,599 --> 00:03:15,699
Do you need to go to the hospital for a check?

50
00:03:15,699 --> 00:03:18,660
Is there a problem with your integration nerve?

51
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:23,140
You're the one with a nerve problem.

52
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:29,260
Jiang Xile, are you really going to be with that robot?

53
00:03:29,260 --> 00:03:32,600
He has a name called Zhang Ping'an.

54
00:03:33,660 --> 00:03:36,479
I think he's like an emotionless robot.

55
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:39,770
Have you ever seen him emotional?

56
00:03:39,770 --> 00:03:44,233
♫ I thought growing up overnight was a movie plot ♫

57
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:47,880
He has no emotions? Do you have any?

58
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:53,139
Ping'an would cherish every single thing I give him, even if it's just a bucket of fish.

59
00:03:53,139 --> 00:03:56,840
What about you? In the past, you always ignored my feelings.

60
00:03:56,840 --> 00:04:00,880
Now, you bother me for no reason.

61
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:08,439
Ding Ran, I have a shirt to give you.

62
00:04:08,439 --> 00:04:10,096
I don't want it.

63
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,920
This is not an ordinary shirt.

64
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:17,400
I embroidered our names on it.

65
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:24,696
[Xile Ding Ran]
♫ Just noticed I haven't looked at the world closely in a while ♫

66
00:04:24,696 --> 00:04:28,419
♫ The most perfect summer and autumn are already yesterday ♫

67
00:04:28,419 --> 00:04:33,119
Jiang Xile, are you trying to piss me off?

68
00:04:33,119 --> 00:04:36,828
♫ Only a few vague images remain ♫

69
00:04:36,828 --> 00:04:38,780
♫ I wish I could return to that year ♫

70
00:04:38,780 --> 00:04:41,400
That shirt was something Xu Shanshan insisted on borrowing.

71
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,780
She asked you for it and you gave it to her?

72
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:45,619
I don't want to talk to you.

73
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:49,080
Jiang Xile, did you bet with someone on graduation day…

74
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:04,179
Ding Ran, you pervert.

75
00:05:04,179 --> 00:05:05,820
Come here.

76
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:07,900
- I didn't mean it.
- Come here, come here.

77
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:11,440
We didn't see them after a round.

78
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:15,660
I've told you already. Young people have their own lives. Don't interfere too much.

79
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:18,440
Let's just consider it as taking a walk to digest the food after dinner.

80
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:22,000
- Okay, every night from now on, we will go for a walk, okay?
- Okay.

81
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,780
Stop right there.

82
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:25,240
I didn't mean to.

83
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,840
- Ding Ran.
- Isn't that the two of them?

84
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:28,400
- Calm down.
- Come here, you come here.

85
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,960
Why did they start fighting?

86
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:33,359
- No, I didn't mean it.
- Stop right there.

87
00:05:33,359 --> 00:05:35,980
My God, their relationship seems so bad.

88
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:37,580
We need to think of a solution quickly.

89
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:39,660
- You're a pervert.
- I didn't mean it.

90
00:05:39,660 --> 00:05:40,940
That's right.

91
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:42,900
Stop right there.

92
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:45,340
Don't hide.

93
00:05:45,340 --> 00:05:46,699
Stop!

94
00:05:46,699 --> 00:05:48,460
Come here.

95
00:05:55,380 --> 00:05:57,859
Hello, welcome.

96
00:06:04,459 --> 00:06:07,360
Qi Fei, why are you here?

97
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,128
Good morning.

98
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,679
Thank you.

99
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:14,999
Let's have lunch together later.

100
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:17,220
Unfortunately, I have to take photos later.

101
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:20,600
- Then I'll take you there.
- No need, I can go by myself.

102
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:27,700
Today is our first day of officially dating. Of course, I should take you there.

103
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,819
Officially dating?

104
00:06:46,539 --> 00:06:49,640
Qi Fei, give me your right hand.

105
00:06:59,139 --> 00:07:03,240
Look, half of my heart is with you now. You must keep it well

106
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:08,500
until we meet next time. This way, we can officially date.

107
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,016
Okay.

108
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:13,439
You can go back first.

109
00:07:13,439 --> 00:07:14,919
I'm leaving.

110
00:07:14,919 --> 00:07:17,300
You must keep it well.

111
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:20,539
- Bye. Bye.
- Bye.

112
00:07:23,999 --> 00:07:26,879
Such a pure young man.

113
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:29,080
I'm feeling so guilty.

114
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,268
Xiao Ke,

115
00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:40,199
what do you think of this guy?

116
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:43,700
Without my glasses, I can't see clearly.

117
00:08:05,619 --> 00:08:09,719
- Here, eat this.
- Uncle Ding, I'm done eating. I'm leaving.

118
00:08:09,719 --> 00:08:13,579
- You've only eaten a little. Finish before leaving.
- I really can't eat anymore.

119
00:08:13,579 --> 00:08:16,880
Ding Ran, did you bully your sister again? She doesn't even want to have a meal with you.

120
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:21,379
- What does it have to do with me?
- No, no. I'm just about to be late for work.

121
00:08:21,379 --> 00:08:23,779
- About to be late? Let Ding Ran drive you there.
- I can go by myself.

122
00:08:23,779 --> 00:08:26,720
- I can go by myself.
- Ding Ran, take your sister to work.

123
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:30,560
She used to be late for school all the time. Being late for work is normal.

124
00:08:36,199 --> 00:08:38,580
What to do?

125
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:44,400
I'm really about to be late. It's hard to hail a cab at this time.

126
00:08:45,219 --> 00:08:48,580
Stop eating. Your sister is about to be late and you're still eating.

127
00:08:49,139 --> 00:08:51,960
Jiang Xile, are you okay? What nerve did you get wrong?

128
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:55,940
Ding Ran, hurry up and take your sister to work.

129
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:02,780
Brother, this is so embarrassing.

130
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:07,739
- Jiang Xile, wait for me.
- Brother, you're so fierce.

131
00:09:07,739 --> 00:09:09,520
I'm so scared.

132
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,139
Xile, come back early after work.

133
00:09:12,139 --> 00:09:14,540
Okay, Uncle Ding.

134
00:09:22,179 --> 00:09:26,680
- You did it on purpose, didn't you?
- Yes, I did it on purpose.

135
00:09:28,079 --> 00:09:30,740
There's a bus stop ahead. It's also convenient to hail a cab.

136
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:33,100
Go to work by yourself in a while.

137
00:09:35,319 --> 00:09:39,439
Uncle Ding, my brother said he'd let…

138
00:09:39,439 --> 00:09:41,800
Company address.

139
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:45,140
Brother, I tricked you. I didn't call your dad.

140
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:48,959
I'll send the company address to our family group chat later.

141
00:09:58,019 --> 00:09:59,960
Keep it well until the next time we meet.

142
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,679
What does she mean?

143
00:10:02,679 --> 00:10:07,340
Does she want to date me

144
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,900
Junior President Qi, you've been coming over to inspect frequently recently.

145
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:24,100
Is there something wrong with our property department?

146
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,700
Nothing, go on with your work.

147
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:41,100
[Outpatient Department]

148
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:44,300
Dr. Ding, Jiang Xile's medical report.

149
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:46,400
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

150
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,350
[Ultrasound Examination Report]

151
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:56,610
[Pathological Diagnosis: Left breast lump aspirate fibroadenoma]

152
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:17,260
Jiang Xile, it's me.

153
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:21,000
Ding Ran, be honest with me. Is it cancer?

154
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,600
Has it spread?

155
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,300
No, it's just--

156
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:28,000
Just have to cut off the breast, right?

157
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:33,400
Don't panic. It's not that serious.

158
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:36,600
You have a breast fibroadenoma. A timely surgery will be enough.

159
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:39,500
It's going to require surgery and you say it's not serious?

160
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:42,500
I rarely even get colds or fevers.

161
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:47,000
Your fibroadenoma is currently 2.2 centimeters in diameter, which is clinically normal size.

162
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,400
It's a benign tumor. The chance of it becoming malignant is low.

163
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,700
Under normal circumstances, surgery will be enough.

164
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,900
All right.

165
00:11:56,600 --> 00:12:01,000
I told Turtle Zhang the name Dark Cloud was ominous.

166
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,300
Jiang Xile,

167
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:08,000
rest assured, it will be fine.

168
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:23,300
Is it Vivi or Kiki?

169
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,600
Vivi? Kiki?

170
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:29,400
Is it on the left or right?

171
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,100
Vivi.

172
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,400
[Family Happiness]

173
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,800
[Jiang Xile]

174
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:04,100
[Send Friend Request]

175
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:09,000
What excuse should I use to add her on WeChat?

176
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,800
[We need to talk about the surgery.]

177
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:19,890
If I say that, she will feel worried.

178
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:21,480
[Add Message]

179
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:37,300
[Jiang Xile requested to add you]

180
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:40,000
She took the initiative to add me.

181
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,500
Please don't let my mom know about the surgery.

182
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,800
She will worry a lot.

183
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,300
- Hello.
- Hello.

184
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:11,500
You're still awake?

185
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:13,500
I can't sleep.

186
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,600
Fibroadenoma patients shouldn't stay up late.

187
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:18,500
Go to sleep early. Did you hear?

188
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:22,400
You have to be hospitalized for a checkup tomorrow. Good night.

189
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:27,000
Ding Ran, please don't hang up.

190
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,400
I still have some questions to ask you.

191
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,000
All right.

192
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:35,000
Will this surgery take a long time?

193
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:39,500
Yours won't. Approximately an hour.

194
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:42,200
Will it leave a scar?

195
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:45,200
There might be one.

196
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,300
But this kind of scar can be treated and removed with medication.

197
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,500
- But...
- No buts.

198
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:55,300
You have to be hospitalized for a checkup tomorrow. Go to sleep early, did you hear?

199
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:59,100
All right, I understand. Good night.

200
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:00,700
Good night.

201
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:39,200
Baby, are you going to work so early?

202
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:43,800
Mom, it's only seven o'clock. Why are you up so early?

203
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:48,600
I made an appointment with your Uncle Ding. Starting today, we're going for morning runs.

204
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,700
Exercising is good for health.

205
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:52,900
Exercise?

206
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:55,500
You won't keep doing it for three days.

207
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:58,100
Don't underestimate me.

208
00:15:58,100 --> 00:16:00,600
Why are you taking a suitcase?

209
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:05,600
I'm going to...

210
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,500
Are you going on a trip with Xiao Zhang?

211
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,500
When did you start dating?

212
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:13,000
No, Mom, I'm not dating him.

213
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,900
Don't be shy. I like Zhang very much.

214
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:21,500
- Xiao Ran, good morning.
- Auntie Baobei, good morning.

215
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:24,200
Today, the employees in Jiang Xile's company are going for team building.

216
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:28,200
She called me last night and asked me to pick her up. Isn't that right, Jiang Xile?

217
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:32,200
Yes, yes. A free driver, why not take advantage?

218
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,400
Thank you, Xiao Ran.

219
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:36,800
Baby, why are you troubling Xiao Ran again?

220
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:39,500
Let's go, Jiang Xile. Otherwise, I'll be late too.

221
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:42,000
All right. Mom, we're leaving.

222
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,400
- All right, take care.
- Bye.

223
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,300
Thank you.

224
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:56,600
Thanks for what you did just now. Give me the suitcase. I'll take it myself.

225
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:59,400
It's okay. Let me help you.

226
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:07,600
You don't have to take me to the hospital later. I can go by myself.

227
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:10,900
I'm not just here to take you. It's on the way.

228
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,200
Xile.

229
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:31,400
Ping'an, didn't I tell you not to come? Why did you really come?

230
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:35,500
It's okay. Your house is close to my office. The hospital is also on the way.

231
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:41,000
Ding Ran, I…

232
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,600
It's best if someone can take you.

233
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:45,200
Mr. Ding, this is Xile's stuff, right?

234
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,900
I'll take it.

235
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:10,300
It's mine. I'll take it.

236
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:16,800
Thank you, Mr. Ding.

237
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:20,400
Xile, let me help you.

238
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:25,000
Ding Ran, Ping'an knows it

239
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:28,900
- because we planned to have dinner together this weekend.
- It's okay.

240
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,800
I'm leaving then.

241
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,400
Okay.

242
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:59,600
You lost, you know?

243
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,900
You're no help at all.

244
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:10,900
Tissues, wet wipes, toothbrush, towel. We have everything.

245
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:15,200
Xile, if you're missing anything, tell me. I'll go buy it.

246
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,800
No need. Ping'an, you should go to work.

247
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:20,400
If I really need something, I'll go buy it myself.

248
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:23,500
A comb. I'll go buy one for you now.

249
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:27,400
No need, Ping'an. I brought my own comb.

250
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:32,400
When are you having your pre-surgery check? I'll accompany you.

251
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,600
No need, really no need.

252
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:38,700
Young lady, having surgery alone is tough.

253
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:41,700
Let your boyfriend accompany you.

254
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:45,400
Exactly. We'd love to find someone to accompany us.

255
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:48,900
No, no, we're not…

256
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:51,400
You're being shy.

257
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:55,000
Jiang Jiang.

258
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,900
- Are you calling me?
- Can I call you Jiang Jiang from now on?

259
00:19:57,900 --> 00:20:00,000
Sure, whatever you want.

260
00:20:00,079 --> 00:20:01,656
Ping'an...

261
00:20:02,739 --> 00:20:06,139
It's such a minor surgery. I can go for the pre-surgery checkup myself tomorrow.

262
00:20:06,139 --> 00:20:09,660
- You should quickly go to work.
- No worries, I've already taken the day off.

263
00:20:09,660 --> 00:20:13,879
You should quickly cancel your leave. I'm only having the pre-surgery checkup tomorrow.

264
00:20:15,739 --> 00:20:19,460
Besides, for this surgery,

265
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:24,539
you being there would actually make it inconvenient.

266
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:30,940
I... I didn't even think of this. Well, take good care of yourself.

267
00:20:30,940 --> 00:20:33,619
- I'll be going then.
- Okay.

268
00:20:37,759 --> 00:20:39,660
This young man is really handsome.

269
00:20:39,660 --> 00:20:41,680
Yeah, this young man is really good.

270
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:43,740
So clean and nice.

271
00:20:43,740 --> 00:20:44,860
Yes, indeed.

272
00:20:44,860 --> 00:20:47,019
[Inpatient Building]

273
00:20:47,019 --> 00:20:48,660
Dr. Ding, you haven't gone home yet?

274
00:20:48,660 --> 00:20:50,799
- I'm on duty tonight.
- Okay.

275
00:21:06,439 --> 00:21:08,480
Where did she go?

276
00:21:13,879 --> 00:21:16,300
Hello, the number you have dialed is busy now.

277
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:18,500
Why isn't she answering the call?

278
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:30,600
Jiang Xile, what are you doing here?

279
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:33,480
I was just talking to my mom on the phone. It's so late.

280
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:36,560
I didn't want to disturb others. So I came up here.

281
00:21:37,179 --> 00:21:38,640
It's okay.

282
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:41,779
After you finish your call, go back to rest.

283
00:21:42,460 --> 00:21:44,160
Ding Ran.

284
00:21:46,959 --> 00:21:48,359
What's wrong?

285
00:21:48,359 --> 00:21:51,119
It's my first time staying in a hospital.

286
00:21:51,119 --> 00:21:54,260
I don't know the two aunties in the ward.

287
00:21:54,260 --> 00:21:56,799
I don't want to stay in there.

288
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:11,460
Then I'll stay with you for a while.

289
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:19,020
Ding Ran, are you the one performing the surgery?

290
00:22:19,020 --> 00:22:21,099
Yes, why?

291
00:22:21,099 --> 00:22:24,000
Don't you think due to our relationship,

292
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:27,440
you doing the surgery for me is a bit awkward?

293
00:22:28,279 --> 00:22:30,160
What's our relationship?

294
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:34,559
We... just... well...

295
00:22:34,559 --> 00:22:39,979
That day at the hospital, when I found out you were the one doing the examination, really awkward.

296
00:22:39,979 --> 00:22:42,320
Didn't you feel awkward?

297
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:52,500
For me, aside from being surprised that the patient I saw that day was you,

298
00:22:54,139 --> 00:22:56,440
I didn't feel awkward at all.

299
00:22:57,800 --> 00:23:02,540
This is my job. So whether it's the breast or other parts,

300
00:23:02,540 --> 00:23:05,800
to me, they're just parts of a person's body.

301
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:08,799
But how can they be the same?

302
00:23:08,799 --> 00:23:11,860
It's like the skin contact between hands.

303
00:23:11,860 --> 00:23:15,499
If I explain it this way, can you understand?

304
00:23:18,380 --> 00:23:20,172
Give me your hand.

305
00:23:25,179 --> 00:23:29,320
Like now, I'm holding your hand like this. Do you feel awkward?

306
00:23:30,299 --> 00:23:34,539
To be honest, a little.

307
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:46,480
Well, can I not have the surgery?

308
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:49,460
Can medication make the tumor disappear?

309
00:23:50,379 --> 00:23:52,180
You don't need to worry so much.

310
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:55,639
This is just a minor surgery.

311
00:23:57,119 --> 00:23:59,760
I promise you'll be fine.

312
00:23:59,760 --> 00:24:03,259
But what if something happens?

313
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:09,640
When my dad had surgery, they all said it'd be fine.

314
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:13,059
But in the end…

315
00:24:18,139 --> 00:24:21,479
Forget it. I should go back to sleep.

316
00:24:24,860 --> 00:24:26,640
Jiang Xile,

317
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:34,720
give me your hand.

318
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,759
You…

319
00:24:36,759 --> 00:24:41,590
♫ I look at you from behind ♫

320
00:24:41,590 --> 00:24:44,920
[Successful Surgery]

321
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:49,159
- What are you doing?
- This is a medal that will ensure your surgery goes smoothly.

322
00:24:49,159 --> 00:24:55,896
[Successful Surgery]
♫ You ignored that sleep talk-like monologue ♫

323
00:24:55,896 --> 00:25:01,270
[Ding Ran]
♫ I rely on you outside of your world ♫

324
00:25:01,270 --> 00:25:03,380
[Inpatient Department]

325
00:25:03,380 --> 00:25:07,879
♫ You are the love that's out of reach ♫

326
00:25:07,879 --> 00:25:10,068
It's stamped.

327
00:25:10,068 --> 00:25:12,720
♫ But I'm waiting like a child ♫

328
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:15,420
Why are you suddenly so nice to me?

329
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:18,039
Because you are my…

330
00:25:18,039 --> 00:25:19,450
What?

331
00:25:19,450 --> 00:25:23,930
♫ Endless like sailing, not afraid of being blown away by the wind ♫

332
00:25:23,930 --> 00:25:28,019
Family. We're about to become family.

333
00:25:28,019 --> 00:25:31,540
♫ How did I meet you? ♫

334
00:25:31,540 --> 00:25:34,480
Let's go, we should go back.

335
00:25:35,954 --> 00:25:42,552
♫ The past, present, and future have all stopped for you ♫

336
00:25:42,552 --> 00:25:49,724
[Successful Surgery]
♫ As you walk towards me, dreams are pushed aside ♫

337
00:25:49,724 --> 00:25:54,644
♫ Grant me the chance to no longer face the crowd ♫

338
00:25:54,644 --> 00:25:57,620
♫ How did I meet you? ♫

339
00:25:57,620 --> 00:26:01,819
♫ Flipping through the pages of our story ♫

340
00:26:01,819 --> 00:26:03,800
Okay, Dr. Ding.

341
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:09,330
♫ Even if the sea in the palm of my hand is empty, I will not let go ♫

342
00:26:09,339 --> 00:26:16,299
♫ Even if the storm comes again, I don't want to hide ♫

343
00:26:16,299 --> 00:26:21,264
♫ Under your eaves, we meet without feeling like strangers now ♫

344
